<tr>
	<td valign="middle">
		<span style="font-family:arial;font-size:12pt;font-weight:bold;">True Combat R.I.P.</span><span class="small">&nbsp;&nbsp;by G.Bloke at 18:36:02 GMT</span>
	</td>
</tr>
<tr>
	<td valign="middle">
		<p>I&#39;ve just learnt that the uber-realistic and extremely promising Quake 3 mod &#39;True Combat&#39; is not to be completed. It seems a lack of motivated team members has forced the project leaders to ditch their plans. <img src="https://assets.aq2world.com/archive/websites/www.actiongames.co.uk/actiongames/smilies/sad.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="">
<br>
<br>True Combat didn&#39;t have unique subject matter, it was similar in many ways to Counter Strike, Urban Terror etc However its redeeming feature was the attention to detail and realism. The maps were designed to be as much like a real-life setting as possible, some were simply beautiful in design. The weapons, player movement and gameplay were also tweaked to give an overall environment that is still missing in many other popular mods.
<br>
<br>The 0.45 Beta version is still available from <a href="http://www.truecombat.com" target="_BLANK" class="pagelink">http://www.truecombat.com</a> and is worth a look. It may be that the project is revived at some point in the future.</p>
	</td>
</tr>
<tr>
	<td valign="middle" align="right">
